The paper focuses on the challenges and solutions for wireless communication at millimeter wave frequencies, which is a topic closely related to the field of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the coordination between physical and transport layers, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of high-quality video streaming and virtual and augmented reality, which are applications related to multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the impact of channel reliability on end-to-end performance, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of input traces generated from measurements from real devices, which is a topic in computer architecture (cs.AR).
